  "text": "To confirm that SCM (K562) accurately predicts true chromatin accessibility, we calculated the overlap between K562 DHS [CITATION_1] ) and thresholded SCM-predicted peaks on Chromosome 14, finding that SCM accurately predicts 72.4% of DHS at a 1% false-discovery rate (area under ROC curve [AUC] = 0.979; PPV 0.479; TPR 0.340, under a rebalanced data set) (Fig.  1D ). Among these DHS, SCM (K562) is accurate over many types of genomic regions, such as predicted enhancers, promoters, and other active chromatin types (Supplemental Fig. 5; [CITATION_2] , indicating that the SCM accurately predicts sites representing a variety of classes of predicted functional chromatin accessibility.",
